First, we find the area of triangle $ABC$.  Using Heron's formula, we have $s = \frac{13+12+5}{2}=15$, so the area of triangle $ABC$ is \[\sqrt{15(15-13)(15-12)(15-5)} = \sqrt{15 \cdot 2 \cdot 3 \cdot 10} = 30.\][asy]
pair A,B,C,N,K,M,J;
A=(0,5);
B=(12,0);
C=(0,0);
N=(5,0);
M=(0,4);
J=(0.35,4.84);
