draw(A--B--C--cycle,linewidth(0.7));
draw(N--K,linewidth(0.7));
draw(M--J,linewidth(0.7));
label("$A$",A,NW);
label("$M$",M,W);
label("$C$",C,SW);
label("$N$",N,S);
label("$B$",B,SE);
label("$K$",K,NE);
label("$J$",J,NE);
label("$13$",(A+B)/2,NE);
label("$12$",(B+C)/2,SE);
label("$5$",(A+C)/2,W);
[/asy]

Now, since $CM=CN=4$, we have that triangles $CMN$ and $ABC$ are similar.  The ratio of corresponding sides is $4/5$, so the area of triangle $CMN$ is $\left(\frac{4}{5}\right)^2 \cdot 30 = \frac{96}{5}$.

